songs.title: Swap Meet
songs.lyrics:
[Chorus]
Your love like gold, what you charging?
Just keep it low 'cause that's a bargain
Tellin' me so and I went all in
Just keep it low 'cause that's a bargain

[Verse 1]
Yeah, that's a bargain
I don't mind, I want your time, just name your price
And I want all in
I don't mind, and if you mind I'll buy you twice
Change your view on a bad day
You just might be my last chance
You worth more than cash

[Chorus]
Your love like gold, and what you charging?
Just keep it low 'cause that's a bargain
Tellin' me so and I went all in
Just keep it low 'cause that's a bargain (Yeah yeah, uh)

[Verse 2]
She needed space, yeah
She left her man and got a spot in Silver Lake, yeah
That's silver lining, see perfections in mistakes, yeah
Try not to say, yeah
Know that you tarnish when you sit there with that blank stare, yeah
I clean you up myself
Won't have you on the shelf
And treat you like an antique
I hope you understand me 'cause
Shit, I'm sold on you

[Outro]
I don't mind, I'll buy your time, I'm sold on you
I don't mind, I'll buy your time, 'cause I'm sold on you, you
